---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Pierce Moore — Writing"
  description="Postmortems and notes from a senior DevOps engineer. Currently archiving the inbox; new entries shipping soon."
>
  <section class="page-gutter pt-32 pb-24 max-w-prose">
    <div class="label-mono mb-3">/ writing</div>
    <h1 class="display-roman text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">postmortems and notes — coming soon.</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-base text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
      I'm pulling postmortems forward from the last two years and rewriting the
      ones worth sharing. They'll land here as I clear them. Pieces in flight:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 font-mono text-sm text-ink-dim">
      <li>· nyc etcd self-removal recovery (rke2, multi-node)</li>
      <li>· emptyDir + postgres: how it actually fails</li>
      <li>· venue provisioning pattern: terraform → ansible → jenkins</li>
      <li>· ~64% aws cost reduction, in three passes</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-8 display-italic text-ink-muted">
      Until then, the FAQ on the home page is the static version of <q>what i think.</q>
    </p>
    <div class="mt-10">
      <a href="/" class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-accent border border-[color:var(--accent-dim)] px-4 py-2 hover:border-[color:var(--accent)]">← return home</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
